1. Interest Rate Environment

| Rate Environment | Bond Type                   | Action Bias       | Reason                               |
| ---------------- | --------------------------- | ----------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Rates falling    | Non-callable, long duration | **Buy**           | Positive convexity, max price upside |
| Rates falling    | Callable                    | **Sell**          | Negative convexity, call risk        |
| Rates rising     | Any long-duration bond      | **Sell / Reduce** | Duration risk dominates              |
| Rates rising     | Short-duration / FRB        | **Hold / Buy**    | Limited price sensitivity            |
| Stable rates     | Callable (high coupon)      | **Hold**          | Carry strategy works                 |
| Stable rates     | Non-callable                | **Hold**          | Limited valuation change             |


2. Credit Fundamentals
| Credit Trend          | Bond Type    | Action Bias       | Reason                             |
| --------------------- | ------------ | ----------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Credit improving      | Non-callable | **Buy / Hold**    | Spread compression + upside        |
| Credit improving      | Callable     | **Sell**          | Higher call probability            |
| Credit deteriorating  | Any          | **Sell**          | Asymmetric downside risk           |
| Credit watch negative | Any          | **Reduce / Sell** | Spread widening precedes downgrade |


3. Liquidity Conditions

| Liquidity Condition | Cash Need       | Action Bias    | Reason                        |
| ------------------- | --------------- | -------------- | ----------------------------- |
| Liquidity stress    | No              | **Hold**       | Avoid forced selling          |
| Liquidity stress    | Yes (near-term) | **Sell**       | Liquidity overrides valuation |
| Normal liquidity    | No              | **Hold / Buy** | Prices reflect fundamentals   |


4. Inflation Regime (Real Returns)

| Inflation Trend   | Bond Type                | Action Bias    | Reason                |
| ----------------- | ------------------------ | -------------- | --------------------- |
| Inflation rising  | Long-duration fixed-rate | **Sell**       | Real returns negative |
| Inflation rising  | Short-duration           | **Hold / Buy** | Faster repricing      |
| Inflation rising  | Floating-rate / ILB      | **Buy**        | Inflation protection  |
| Inflation falling | Long-duration            | **Buy**        | Disinflation tailwind |


5. Callable Bondâ€“Specific Overlay (Most Important)

This overrides many other signals.
| Situation                         | Action Bias      |
| --------------------------------- | ---------------- |
| Yield-to-call < Yield-to-maturity | **Sell**         |
| Near call date + falling rates    | **Sell**         |
| Rising rates + callable bond      | **Hold**         |
| Issuer has history of calling     | **Avoid / Sell** |
